1 olive oil
2 potato
1 packet chicken breast
1 packet Chargrilled Capsicum Relish
1 tomato
1 bag salad leaves
1 drizzle balsamic vinegar
1 sachet Nan's Special Seasoning
1 packet Greek salad cheese/feta cheese
½ apple

• Preheat oven to 220°/200°C fan-forced. Cut potato into bite-sized chunks.
• Place potato and Nan’s special seasoning on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil and season with pepper. Toss to coat, then spread out in a single layer. Roast until tender, 25-30 minutes.

• Meanwhile, cut deep slices (taking care to not slice all the way through) across chicken breast at 1cm intervals.
• Season chicken with salt and pepper and place, cut-side up, on a second lined oven tray. Spoon over chargrilled capsicum relish, then crumble with cheese.
• Place chicken on lower oven shelf and bake until cooked through, 12-16 minutes.

TIP: Chicken is cooked through when it’s no longer pink inside.

While chicken is baking, roughly chop tomato. Thinly slice apple (see ingredients).
• In a large bowl, combine tomato, apple, mixed salad leaves, a drizzle of olive oil and a drizzle of balsamic vinegar. Season to taste and toss to coat.

• Divide hasselback chicken and spiced potatoes between plates.
• Serve with apple salad.